R Markdown

This is an R Markdown document. Markdown is a simple formatting syntax for authoring HTML, PDF, and MS Word documents. For more details on using R Markdown see http://rmarkdown.rstudio.com.

When you click the Knit button a document will be generated that includes both content as well as the output of any embedded R code chunks within the document. You can embed an R code chunk like this:

library(MASS)
help(cats)
summary(cats)
##  Sex         Bwt             Hwt       
##  F:47   Min.   :2.000   Min.   : 6.30  
##  M:97   1st Qu.:2.300   1st Qu.: 8.95  
##         Median :2.700   Median :10.10  
##         Mean   :2.724   Mean   :10.63  
##         3rd Qu.:3.025   3rd Qu.:12.12  
##         Max.   :3.900   Max.   :20.50

Including Plots

You can also embed plots, for example:

plot(Hwt ~ Bwt, data=cats)
out = lm(Hwt~Bwt, data=cats)
abline(out)

We fit a linear model of the form

\[ y_i = \beta_0 + \beta_1 x_i + e_i,\quad i=1,2,\ldots, n \]

And there you have it!

abline(out)

Here is a summary of the linear model for predicting daughter’s height from mother’s height:

\[ E(Daughter) = \beta_0 + \beta_1 Mother,\quad \hat{\beta_1}=0.54175 \]
